<br>
All I did is park my water pet somewhere safe, run off and find a drake.  I'd pull with shock of blades and haul my little butt back to my pet.  Pet would engage as soon as the AE from the drake hit me, and then I would nuke solid the whole fight till the drake runs.  (obviously it's important for you to stay outside the AE range, no need for the pet AND me to be out of health)<br>
<br>
The pet would always get down to 20% health or less and I would be at about half mana.  By the time he got full health I was at 80% and ready to roll again.<br>
<br>
All in all great exp and the level flew by pretty quick.  Those imps ARE nasty as hell though, stay way away from them at 11 or 12.  Basilisks are mega good experience too but pretty tough.  Maybe now with my new pets they will be easier. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
