<br>
I got there at level 10 and with a damage-shielded air pet was able to break the camp. Holding it was no problem whatsoever. In fact I held it until I went linkdead (had gotten 4.5 bubbles into 10, arrived just after turning 10). Then I was not able to break the camp -- had two failed attempts (wasn't even close). So either the first time was a fluke, or else the Bubble Barrier had kicked in.<br>
<br>
But ... if you cannot break the spawn, jump over to the other island. There are four aqua goblins (not sure on levels, but tend to be lower than the alluring sirens) as well as a single-spawn alluring siren. Attacking the goblins doesn't attract the others, unless of course he gets the chance to run and gets too close to an unengaged one.<br>
<br>
So, if you are unable to break the right island, the left one will be good xp for you as well. When you hit 12, some of the goblins should start being green to you, but by then you'll be able to reliably break the two-spawn sirens (assuming you have your new spells).<br>
<br>
It was so good there that I invited a couple friends of mine (druid and rogue), and even with 3 of us the experience came pretty fast. <p><body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">

